<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880831-0088 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Resorts International Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RT.A </CO><IN> TNM CNO REL </IN><TEXT>   Resorts International Inc. shareholders approved Merv Griffin's $36-a-share bid to acquire all the company's Class A common stock outstanding.    As previously reported, the entertainer and businessman offered to buy the Atlantic City, N.J., hotel-casino company for about $302 million for all Class A and supervoting Class B shares outstanding.    Resorts said that a majority of its Class A shares have been tendered already, but a majority vote in favor of the Griffin proposal was still needed.    Mr. Griffin's Griffco Acquisition Corp. reported Friday that 4,519,478 Class A shares had been tendered. A condition of the merger called for at least 4,086,521 shares to be tendered. There are 5.7 million Class A shares outstanding. </TEXT></DOC>